main event: A person sighted an unidentified object that looked like a Napoleon-shaped object turned sideways over Wilberforce, Ohio on November 6, 1967.
interesting points: The object was observed for 10-15 seconds and appeared to be hovering at first, then quickly flew away.
The object was estimated to be at an altitude of 600-700 feet and made no sound.
The witness's car stopped when the object was observed, indicating possible electrical or magnetic effects.
Several other people in the area reported seeing similar objects around the same time period.
The witness tried to take pictures but was unable to do so, possibly due to mist or fog in the air.
witnesses: Some construction workers and the report author
photographs: No, the report indicates the witness was unable to take photographs
